#audio data needs to be slice to trunck between 5-10 seconds

1.create python 3.11 env
（currently, I'm using a vitural environment named SCV, flowing the steps 
   # create a folder to install the virtual environment 
   # execute "python -m venv  nameofspace ", to create the venv
   # switch to the space ,inside the virtual folder path ,execute " source nameofspace/bin/activate"
   # then use normal python cmd, such as pip install
   # how to transfer this venv remains exploration ???
）

2.clone this repo  https://github.com/openvpi/audio-slicer.git
3.install packages:
_pip3 install -r requirments.txt_
_pip3 install librosa_
_pip3 install soundfile_

4.edit file "run.py", change in_dir and out_dir
5.run "run.py"
